<h1>Accessibility Statement</h1>
<span class="updated">Last updated: May 15, 2026</span>

<p>Near and Far Events is committed to making our Service accessible to people of all abilities. We aim to conform with the <strong>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 Level AA</strong>.</p>

<h2>What We've Done</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Semantic HTML structure for screen readers</li>
  <li>Keyboard navigation support throughout the Service</li>
  <li>Sufficient color contrast for text against backgrounds</li>
  <li>Descriptive link text rather than vague labels like "click here"</li>
  <li>Form fields with associated labels</li>
  <li>Mobile-responsive design that adapts to screen size</li>
  <li>No information conveyed by color alone</li>
  <li>Alt text on meaningful images (icons that aren't decorative)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Known Limitations</h2>
<p>We're working on:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Improving screen-reader announcements for modal dialogs</li>
  <li>Higher-contrast mode option</li>
  <li>Comprehensive automated accessibility testing</li>
  <li>Regular manual audits by accessibility professionals</li>
</ul>

<h2>Reporting Accessibility Issues</h2>
<p>If you experience a barrier on Near and Far Events, please let us know. Your feedback helps us prioritize fixes.</p>
<div class="contact-box">
  <p>Email: <a href="mailto:hello@nearandfarevents.com">hello@nearandfarevents.com</a><br>
  Subject line: "Accessibility"<br>
  Please include the page where you encountered the issue and a description of the barrier.</p>
</div>

<h2>Our Commitment</h2>
<p>We treat accessibility issues seriously and will respond within 5 business days. Critical access barriers will be prioritized for fix.</p>

<h2>Third-Party Content</h2>
<p>Some pages link to external sites (ticketing partners, event organizer websites, etc.). We cannot guarantee the accessibility of third-party content but we are happy to help you reach event organizers directly if needed.</p>
</div>

